Improve Search Results with Einstein Semantic Search

Turn on semantic search to improve relevance, reduce “no results found” pages, lower bounce rates, and increase conversion rates. Einstein semantic search accounts for synonyms, alternate spellings, abbreviations, typos, and product themes, improving your search results.

Where: This change applies to B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

When: Semantic search is available in North America and Europe and will be available in the Asia-Pacific region in Summer ’24.

How: From Store Settings, select Commerce Einstein, and then turn on Commerce Einstein and Semantic Search. Rebuild your search index to start seeing results.
title: Improve Search Results with Einstein Semantic Search
